<h1>Problem 1872 - 2023 Mediterranean Mathematics Competition, P4 of 4, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>Let \(d(n)\) denote the number of divisors of \(n\). A sequence \(a_1,a_2,\dots\) of positive integers is called double-sequence if <ul><li>\(a_k\mid a_{k+1}\)</li><li>\(d\left(a_{k+1}\right)=2d\left(a_k\right)\)</li></ul>
for all \(k=1,2,\dots\) . A positive number \(n\) is called good if for every double-sequence with \(a_1=n\) we have that \(a_{k+1}/{a_k}\) is a prime power for \(k=1,2,\dots\) . Prove that a number \(n\) is good if and only if \(n\) appears in a double-sequence with \(a_1=1\).</p>
